final int phasedFirstAlleleIndex = phaseGT.equals(phase10) ? 0 : 1;
if (g.isHet() && ! isSiteSpecificAltAllele(newAlleles.get(phasedFirstAlleleIndex))) {
    Collections.reverse(newAlleles);
}

I would also consider making the phase GTs into an enum instead of hardcoded strings, and giving it a method to extract which index, 0 or 1, is first.

